data.name: How Will I Know by Whitney Houston
data.description: Multi-Grammy Winner and Whitney Houston’s frequent produce and songwriter relates the story behind creating her smash: “How Will I Know”. Released in 1985, "How Will I Know" became Houston's second No.1 single on the United States Billboard Hot 100, and was a worldwide success reaching the top 10 in Ireland, Norway, Sweden and the United Kingdom, as well as hitting the top 20 in the Netherlands, New Zealand, and Switzerland.

data.name: Nowhere to Run by Martha & The Vandellas
data.description: One of the most successful songwriter/producers of the rock era, Lamont Dozier, relays his inspiration for writing "Nowhere to Run," the 1967 song that spoke to both the civil rights movement and the growing conflict in Vietnam.

data.name: Anytime by Brian McKnight
data.description: Brian McKnight, the master of the quiet storm, explains the process of writing his modern day saloon song "Anytime." Released in 1997, the album, by the same name, broke the top 20 on the Billboard 200 chart and took the No.1 position for three weeks on the Top R&B Albums Chart.
